---
description: Dashboard, detail, prep, and rail contract.
globs:
  - "app/dashboard/**/*.tsx"
  - "app/jobs/**/*.tsx"
  - "components/dashboard/**/*.tsx"
  - "components/jobs/**/*.tsx"
  - "components/navigation/**/*.tsx"
  - "app/styles/dashboard.css"
  - "app/styles/responsive.css"
alwaysApply: true
---

Use the shared dashboard/job-flow contract:

- left rail + main queue/detail surface stay on the same structural grid
- queue rows, detail pages, and prep pages share layout language instead of diverging
- blank-profile lock must be truthful across Potential, left rail, detail, and prep
- workflow actions should only appear when upstream state truly supports them

When editing these surfaces:
- prefer shared job-flow or stage-row fixes over per-page drift
- keep copy and behavior consistent across queue, detail, prep, and rail
- do not redesign the visual system while doing cleanup
